summary: “Letting Go” Hi! I made a video work up on vimeo for anyone to view and just check out-  All images are re-arranged out of the...
caption:
“Letting Go”
Hi! I made a video work up on vimeo for anyone to view and just check out-  All images are re-arranged out of the Cinematic Drama, Penny Dreadful. I not only hope you can check it out, its visibility is based on an Introduction to Digital Composition - both ways, for the characterization, the compositional practice, and..organization of meaning… because Digital Imagery has a conversation more and more about the way Images are bleeding into less tactile, more original aesthetic; this piece I hope if not as stand a lone, be  direct reference to the ecology of digital imaging, processing and compositional scoring… using digital composition… as a means.

summary: [Image Description: A “Meet The Artist” meme done digitally. On the right of the page is a drawing of the artist, Robin. He’s an...
body:
[Image Description: A “Meet The Artist” meme done digitally. On the right of the page is a drawing of the artist, Robin. He’s an olive skinned person with a curly, dyed purple undercut and dark brown eyes framed by clear glasses. He has a stud earring, and a horseshoe septum ring. He’s wearing an Evanescence beanie that gradients from black to light gray, a white binder that he tucked into his black skinny jeans, a red flannel, and gray, high top vans. He has one hand on his hip, the other gesturing upwards towards the information written about him to his left. 

Just above the hand that is pointing upwards, there’s a small rainbow infinity symbol signifying that the Robin is autistic. Above that is the Puerto Rican flag, indicating that Robin is Puerto Rican.

On the left side of the page is writing about the artist himself that reads:

Meet The Artist

Robin - 20 - They/He

Virgo - Sep 9 - A drawing of the Transgender Symbol

There are four hearts under that text, and inside the four hearts are different pride flags for identities Robin holds, in the following order: Transgender, Nonbinary, Asexual, Bisexual

Under the hearts, there is a gray rectangle with more text indicating Robin’s likes and dislikes.

Likes Include: Comic Books

D & D (Dungeons and Dragons)

Critical Role

The Adventure Zone

Game Grumps

High Top Shoes

Big Sweaters

Dislikes Include: Spiders

Winter/Snow

Loud Noises

Math of all kinds

Holes (I’m trypophobic)

Driving

Rude Customers

End Description]

I finally got around to doing a “Meet The Artist” meme, which I’ve wanted to do for years now, but haven’t. But I’ve decided that 2019 is going to be the year where I do a bunch of art things that I didn’t get around to doing before, and this is the first step!
